@startuml 07-sequence-authentication
title Authentication Flow — JWT / SSO

actor User
participant "Frontend App" as UI
participant "API Gateway" as API
participant "Auth Service" as Auth
participant "Identity Provider\n(Okta / Azure AD)" as IDP
database "Redis\n(session cache)" as Redis

== Local JWT Authentication ==

User -> UI : Enter credentials
UI -> API : POST /api/v1/auth/login\n{username, password}
API -> Auth : validateCredentials()
Auth -> Auth : lookup user & roles
Auth -> Auth : sign JWT (HS256, 24h)
Auth --> API : {access_token, user, expires_in}
API --> UI : 200 OK + JWT
UI -> UI : Store token in localStorage
UI --> User : Redirect to Dashboard

== Subsequent API Request ==

User -> UI : View vessel schedule
UI -> API : GET /api/v1/vessels\nAuthorization: Bearer <token>
API -> Auth : JWT Strategy validate()
Auth -> Auth : decode & verify signature
Auth --> API : {userId, roles}
API -> API : RBAC check (vessel:read)
API --> UI : 200 {data: vessels[]}
UI --> User : Display schedule

== SSO Flow (Production) ==

User -> UI : Click "Sign in with SSO"
UI -> IDP : OAuth2 authorize redirect
IDP --> User : Login prompt
User -> IDP : Authenticate
IDP --> UI : Authorization code
UI -> API : POST /auth/callback {code}
API -> IDP : Exchange code for tokens
IDP --> API : ID token + claims
API -> Auth : mapGroupsToRoles()
Auth -> Redis : cache session
API --> UI : Platform JWT
UI --> User : Dashboard

@enduml
